The police on Thursday arraigned a 20-year-old man , David Moses, in a Grade I Area Court Mpape, Abuja, for alleged criminal trespass. The police charged Moses, who resides at Mpape with a one count charge. The police prosecutor, Edwin Ochayi, told the court that one Ezekiel Michael, of Junior Secondary School Mpape, reported the matter at Mpape Police Station on June 21. Ochayi said the complainant reported that on that same date the defendant and others now at large, trespassed into the school premises and the defendant allegedly started making trouble with the school principal. The prosecutor said the offence contravened the provisions of Section 342 of the Penal Code. After the charge was read to him, he pleaded not guilty. The presiding judge, Salihu Ibrahim, admitted the defendant to bail in the sum of N200,000 with one surety in like sum. He ordered that the surety must be a reliable and reasonable person who must reside within the courtâ€™s jurisdiction. The judge adjourned the case until July 17, for further hearing. (NAN)  Police arraign 3 friends for alleged theft Police arraign bizman over alleged N200, 000 fraud Police arraign applicant for allegedly stealing 53 cartons of tiles , 2 Italian doors Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin